—Tsabo Tavoc, Phyrexian general

name: Void
text: Choose a number. Destroy all artifacts and creatures with converted mana cost equal to that number. Then target player reveals his or her hand and discards all nonland cards with converted mana cost equal to the number.

name: Voracious Cobra
text:
First strike
Whenever Voracious Cobra deals combat damage to a creature, destroy that creature.

editions.flavor: There's no known antidote for the cobra's venom . . . or its appetite.

name: Wallop
text: Destroy target blue or black creature with flying.

editions.flavor: In Yavimaya, flying low to join a battle can be a costly mistake.

name: Wandering Stream
text: Domain — You gain 2 life for each basic land type among lands you control.

editions.flavor:
"Dominaria touches us all."
—Molimo, maro-sorcerer

name: Wane
text: Destroy target enchantment.

name: Wash Out
text: Return all permanents of the color of your choice to their owners' hands.

editions.flavor:
"Rest now. You've neither won nor lost, but this battle is over for you just the same."
—Teferi

"It's not the darkness I fear but dull and numbing shades of gray."
—Sydri, galvanic genius

"Perhaps planning should become a higher priority for me."
—Dack Fayden

name: Wax
text: Target creature gets +2/+2 until end of turn.

name: Wayfaring Giant
text: Domain — Wayfaring Giant gets +1/+1 for each basic land type among lands you control.

editions.flavor: Its stature and stride increase with each step it takes.

name: Well-Laid Plans
text: Prevent all damage that would be dealt to a creature by another creature if they share a color.

editions.flavor: "I knew this day would come," said Urza. Looking at the destruction, Barrin sighed, "You don't have to revel in it."

name: Whip Silk
text:
Enchant creature
Enchanted creature has reach. (It can block creatures with flying.)
{G}: Return Whip Silk to its owner's hand.

editions.flavor: Llanowar forges weapons of steel. Yavimaya grows her weapons within.

name: Wings of Hope
text:
Enchant creature
Enchanted creature gets +1/+3 and has flying.

editions.flavor: Urza knew Phyrexians would come through the air and sent his soldiers to greet them.

name: Winnow
text:
Destroy target nonland permanent if another permanent with the same name is on the battlefield.
Draw a card.

editions.flavor:
"Strength in numbers? I think not."
—Gerrard

name: Worldly Counsel
text: Domain — Look at the top X cards of your library, where X is the number of basic land types among lands you control. Put one of those cards into your hand and the rest on the bottom of your library in any order.

editions.flavor: Every horizon hides a new possibility.

name: Yavimaya Barbarian
text: Protection from blue

editions.flavor: Not all elves embrace the pastoral life. Some still roam the forest's edge, forever making war against their hated enemies.

name: Yavimaya Kavu
text:
Yavimaya Kavu's power is equal to the number of red creatures on the battlefield.
Yavimaya Kavu's toughness is equal to the number of green creatures on the battlefield.

editions.flavor: Kavu hunt prey in packs—one kavu hunts a pack of prey.

name: Yawgmoth's Agenda
text:
You can't cast more than one spell each turn.
You may play cards from your graveyard.
If a card would be put into your graveyard from anywhere, exile it instead.

name: Zanam Djinn
text:
Flying
Zanam Djinn gets -2/-2 as long as blue is the most common color among all permanents or is tied for most common.

name: Zap
text:
Zap deals 1 damage to target creature or player.
Draw a card.

editions.flavor: "All this time I thought Squee was useless," chuckled Sisay. "Who knew he'd be such a good shot?"
